entries.femaleVariant: You said you were looking for work.
Got a fight here.
You César? I'm here for my fight.
entries.maleVariant: You Cesar? I'm here for my fight.

entries.femaleVariant: <mothertongue l="mex" m="hijo de puta" b="Yeah, that's me – toughest " a=" in the Glen."/>
Mhm. And the worst father in Night City.
OK, I'll match it.
Too rich for my blood.
What's the car?
Too rich for me... At least for now.
Right, right... Well, you change your mind, you let me know, 'kay?
OK, I'll match it. We good?
So, bare hands only, right? No pullin' any monowires or mantis blades outta your ass?
Careful, now. I don't fuck around.
Stop! Stop the fight! Can't you see he's had enough?!
Micaela, baby... I-I'm sorry... Shit, I--
<mothertongue l="mex" m="pendejo" b="Not another word, you " a=". Hand over the stupid keys and let's go home."/>
Think you had enough, 'ey?
Well, y'know... I'm game for a rematch. I can always use the extra eddies – now, especially.
[Start fight] Ready.
Yep. Ready to rumble.
All right, let's talk. What's the car?
A real gem. A tuned-up 2056 classic, but with only twenty thousand miles on 'er. No dings, no patch jobs...
Uh-huh. And stolen?
All good. Let's go.
And I found it!
No, this isn't work. Have you ever thought what would happen to us if we lost you? Lost all our money?
Either you change, César... or I change the locks.
Listen, I need a lot of scratch and fast. That's why I'm only takin' serious wagers.
Micaela, baby... I know what I'm doin'. You gotta trust--
I'm not talkin' to you. First, you spend a fortune on chrome, and now... Ugh, I give up.
I'm puttin' my ride on the line. Either you match it in cash, or you can forget about the fight.
No, no, no, none of that. She's legit. Give you my word.
Thanks for the new ride.
Give me the cash, but you keep the car.
Pleasure doin' biz. Got rubber to burn.
entries.maleVariant: Pleasure doin' biz. I got rubber to burn.

entries.femaleVariant: <mothertongue l="mex" m="Mierda" b="" a="... She was a beauty..."/>
I'll take my eddies, but you can keep the ride.
You... I mean, really?
Any ideas for a name?
My knight in shining armor... How do we get home now, eh? On foot?!
Nah, you keep the car and the money.
Keep it, everything. Won't take anything from you.
entries.maleVariant: Keep it, everything. I won't take anything from you.

entries.femaleVariant: Micaela! Micaela, wait for fuck's sake!
Listen... You don't like the deal, don't take it. Just don't drag this out. Time is money, and I'm runnin' out of both.
Ugh... Here. Spoil her for me.
Uh-huh... Yeah.
Not my type of joke.
entries.maleVariant: It's not my type of joke.

entries.femaleVariant: Now, the eddies. Before I change my mind.
Listen, I... Shit, I dunno how to thank you...
Then don't thank me.
Just don't lose what you have left.
Then don't.
Just don't lose what you still got left.
Oof... We dodged one there, huh?
Don't intend to.
<mothertongue l="mex" m="Pendejos" b="Mhm. " a=" have all the luck."/>
Hmm... Something with a "V"?
I'll think of something, OK? Just calm down for Christ's sake!
Beat some sense into him for me, OK? He needs a good lesson.
Right.
I ask 'cause last guy I fought tried to surprise me with Longspurs. Anyway, you ready to start?
Keep the eddies. Car's all I want.
Thanks. But the eddies I bet – they're yours.
